The paper deals with revenue maximization in a monopoly setting, which is a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT) and mechanism design (cs.EC). The use of duality techniques suggests a connection to optimization and convex analysis (cs.DS, cs.MA), while the focus on allocation rules and pricing strategies suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT).
